# Campaign Builder — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
Internal tool for Partrunner's growth team to create Meta Ads campaigns for driver recruitment. Conversational wizard guided by "Aurora" AI agent.

## Tech Stack
- Vite 5 + React 18 + TypeScript (strict) + Tailwind CSS 3
- Path alias: `@/` → `src/`
- No CSS files (Tailwind only), no CSS-in-JS
- Functional components only, hooks for state

## API Integration
- Meta Marketing API v21.0 (stubs in `src/services/metaAdsService.ts`)
- Gemini API for image generation (stubs in `src/services/geminiService.ts`)
- Env vars: VITE_META_APP_ID, VITE_META_ACCESS_TOKEN, VITE_META_AD_ACCOUNT_ID, VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY

## Brand Rules (STRICT)
- Colors: #FDD238 (yellow), #000000 (black), #FFFFFF (white) — NO other colors
- Fonts: Bebas Neue (titles, `font-display`), Barlow (body, `font-sans`)
- Tailwind tokens: `pr-yellow`, `pr-black`, `pr-white`
- Logo base URL: https://lrzcturtxtzhdzqacefy.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/Imagenes/
- Dark theme default

## Conventions
- Types in `src/types/`, services in `src/services/`, hooks in `src/hooks/`
- All API functions are async, return typed responses
- Mock data for development, TODO comments for real implementation
- Spanish UI text, English code/comments

## Key Decisions
- Wizard state managed via useWizard hook (no external state lib)
- Campaign history in localStorage
- Toast notifications via useToast hook
- Aurora conversational UI with chat bubbles per step

